                <note rend="inline" type="source">834.00 Revolutions/5: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Howard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-17T09:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 17, 1936—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. Revolutionary movement broke out early this morning. It is rumored that
                    garrison at Paraguari and several local forces, including military school and
                    aviation, have revolted and are said to be marching on Asunción. There is
                    intermittent firing in the center of the city.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Buenos Aires.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Howard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
